nit: we should differentiate this trace message from the duplicate based on index/epoch check. If we're trying to track down why an attestation wasn't gossiped, knowing if it was rejected because it was identical to another attestation or just from the same index/epoch is very useful info.




        Suggested change











                  LOG.trace("Ignoring duplicate aggregate");



                  LOG.trace("Ignoring duplicate aggregate based on hash tree root");

